I just wanted to get in a room with you.

06:21.029 --> 06:23.725
And I wanted to tell
you how proud I am of you.

06:23.865 --> 06:25.662
You've done the city a great favour.

06:25.800 --> 06:28.394
You, in my eyes: hero.

06:28.536 --> 06:30.731
- Thank you.
- Here's the thing.

06:30.872 --> 06:33.102
Some uncomfortable evidence
has come to light.

06:33.241 --> 06:35.004
If it should come out...

06:35.676 --> 06:37.234
...we will be fucked.

06:37.378 --> 06:38.936
And it is a necessity

06:39.080 --> 06:41.048
that we remain un-fucked.

06:41.883 --> 06:42.850
So...

06:42.984 --> 06:44.349
- You're done, Detective.

06:45.253 --> 06:47.585
- Yesenia Barea was 16 years old, Chief.

06:47.722 --> 06:49.917
- Mikey Tavarez was exonerated.
- Yeah, and they got it wrong.

06:50.058 --> 06:53.255
- So you put it right.
- No, I'm not the bad guy, Chief.

06:53.394 --> 06:54.952
Mr. Mayor...
- You keep telling yourself that.

06:55.096 --> 06:56.961
- You see, Billy,
there's some wars you fight,

06:57.098 --> 06:58.759
and some wars you walk away from.

06:58.900 --> 07:01.869
- Mayor...
- This is not the fighting kind.

07:02.003 --> 07:03.698
I have a long memory, son.

07:04.605 --> 07:06.505
If you ever change your number...

07:07.275 --> 07:09.903
...you make sure you let my office know.

07:45.780 --> 07:48.715
