a man that doesn't pay his debts

13:56.050 --> 13:59.679
is the worst kind of man there is.
Is that the kind of man you are?

13:59.820 --> 14:02.186
<i>- Okay, okay.
I can maybe get you half by Monday.</i>

14:02.323 --> 14:05.315
- Alright, half is fair, I can do half.
Talk to Katy.

14:05.926 --> 14:07.484
- Hey, Dave. Katy.

14:08.128 --> 14:10.255
So what time Monday, huh?

14:10.397 --> 14:13.457
- I'm going to get some air.
- Okay.

14:19.707 --> 14:20.731
Billy?!

14:20.875 --> 14:21.933
Billy!

14:22.843 --> 14:25.209
Phone!
- Take a message!

14:25.346 --> 14:26.813
- It's the mayor.

14:35.523 --> 14:37.218
- You seem nervous.

14:37.358 --> 14:40.350
- Yeah, it's probably the bomb
I got shoved up my asshole.

14:42.730 --> 14:45.324
Too soon?
<i>- Councilman Valliant,</i>

14:45.466 --> 14:49.459
any comment on the Bolton Village sale?
- I think this is a sad day for New York.

14:49.603 --> 14:52.629
I never thought I'd see a mayor of this city,
even this mayor,

14:52.773 --> 14:56.265
stoop so low as to steal the homes
of 30,000 hard-working New Yorkers.

14:56.410 --> 14:59.208
And I guarantee you
that I will not let this sale stand

14:59.346 --> 15:00.904
when I'm elected mayor on Tuesday.

15:01.048 --> 15:03.689
<i>- Do you think the timing
of the mayor's announcement is political?</i>

15:03.784 --> 15:04.944
<i>- Absolutely. I know it's political.</i>

15:05.085 --> 15:07.451
<i>And that's not to say
that Nick Hostetler doesn't care,</i>

15:07.588 --> 15:09.789
<i>because evidently he cares very deeply
about two things:</i>

15:09.857 --> 15:12.690
<i>His own job and taking care of his buddies
on Wall Street.</i>

15:12.826 --> 15:15.852
<i>- Do you have a message to the people
of Bolton Village, Councilman?</i>

15:15.996 --> 15:17.623
<i>- Yes, I do. Help is on the way.</i>

15:17.765 --> 15:20.165
<i>Come Tuesday,
you will have an ally in City Hall.</i>

15:20.301 --> 15:22.929
<i>Vote your interests next week,
and we'll take this city back.</i>

15:23.070 --> 15:24.594
- Can't even get his numbers right.

15:24.738 --> 15:29.266
Bolton Village is home to 37,512.
And you know what this deal means for them?

15:29.410 --> 15:32.641
- Valliant seems to think
it means inevitable eviction, Mayor.

15:32.780 --> 15:34.407
- Valliant thinks.

15:35.583 --> 15:38.518
What it means is better service,
more attentive landlords,

15:38.652 --> 15:41.644
somebody actually showing up
when the toilet is blocked

15:41.789 --> 15:43.450
or the heat's on the fritz.

15:43.591 --> 15:46.389
It means paint on the walls
and it means the windows fixed.

15:46.527 --> 15:48.654
- Valliant says Solstein Donagan's
gonna jack up their rents,

15:48.796 --> 15:50.593
replace 'em with yuppies.

15:51.799 --> 15:54.529
- This is a great deal
for the people of Bolton Village,

15:54.668 --> 15:57.466
and it's a great deal
for the city of New York.

15:57.605 --> 16:02.633
- Do you think the announcement of this deal
will, uh, add to your poll numbers, sir?

16:02.776 --> 16:04.641
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>
- Well, you know, Mike,

16:04.778 --> 16:08.680
if the readers of the <i>New York Post</i>
want to reward competence,

16:08.816 --> 16:11.478
who am I to argue with that?
Excuse me.

16:11.619 --> 16:12.813
Yeah.

16:14.054 --> 16:16.818
Well, obviously,
that was some attempt at humour.

16:17.825 --> 16:21.124
No, call off the brigade. Bring him up.
Thank you.

16:21.261 --> 16:24.059
Alright, Mike, get outta here.

16:24.632 --> 16:27.123
Go and do the people's work.
- Good luck Tuesday, Mayor.

16:27.267 --> 16:28.700
- Hey, hey, thank you.

16:28.836 --> 16:31.168
Look - ahem - here's one for the car.
One for the wife.

16:31.305 --> 16:33.933
And that one for the kid.
Put it on his school bag.

16:34.074 --> 16:35.701
- Thanks, Mayor.
- Alright.

16:35.843 --> 16:37.504
<font color="#D900D9">(BACKGROUND CHATTER)</font>
- Mr. Mayor.

16:37.645 --> 16:38.839
- Hey.

16:39.480 --> 16:44.474
You know, Billy, we take threats
of terrorism very seriously around here.

16:45.085 --> 16:48.350
- Right.
- Even from good Catholic boys like you.

16:48.489 --> 16:49.854
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>

16:50.491 --> 16:53.722
I'm only kidding.
Look at you, lookin' all civilized.

16:53.861 --> 16:55.522
- It's good to see you, Mayor.

16:55.663 --> 16:57.722
- See this golden boy on your way in?

16:57.865 --> 16:59.730
- Yeah, I caught a glimpse.

16:59.867 --> 17:01.994
- Y'know, if I'm being honest,

17:02.136 --> 17:04.730
ah... I find it faintly insulting.

17:04.872 --> 17:08.501
- What's that, the fact that you're running
dead even with a nobody?

17:10.310 --> 17:12.835
- Yeah.
You were always were more balls than tact.

17:12.980 --> 17:17.508
- Hey, I don't know what came over me, Mayor.
I'm actually trying to reverse the trend.

17:17.651 --> 17:20.313
- No, you shouldn't.
It's one of your strong suits.

17:20.887 --> 17:23.982
