<font color="#808080">PA:</font> <i>The next and final stop
will be Montauk.</i>

33:56.683 --> 33:59.049
<i>All passengers must depart the train
at Montauk.</i>

33:59.185 --> 34:01.710
<i>Please be sure to gather all...</i>
- Nice talking to you.

34:01.854 --> 34:03.515
- Yeah, you, too.

34:30.149 --> 34:31.844
<font color="#D900D9">(CELLPHONE RINGING)</font>

34:38.157 --> 34:39.886
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT DIALOGUE)</font>

34:51.404 --> 34:52.928
Oh, shit.

35:10.423 --> 35:11.754
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

35:13.025 --> 35:14.822
<font color="#D900D9">(RINGING)</font><font color="#808080">
KATY:</font> <i>Taggart Agency.</i>

35:14.961 --> 35:17.682
- Were you on the other line?
<i>- No, I'm trying to save your business.</i>

35:17.730 --> 35:20.460
- Y'know, I don't get to say this too often,
but you were right.

35:20.600 --> 35:21.828
<i>- Really?</i>

35:21.968 --> 35:25.233
- The mayor's wife
is fucking the campaign manager.

35:25.371 --> 35:26.633
<i>- Told you.</i>
- Call the mayor,

35:26.773 --> 35:28.536
tell him I got some pictures.
<i>- Okay.</i>

35:28.674 --> 35:31.074
- And stay off the fuckin' phone.
<i>- I wasn't a...</i>

35:31.210 --> 35:33.337
<font color="#D900D9">(MELLOW HIP-HOP MUSIC)</font>

35:33.479 --> 35:36.642
- Ryan, I wouldn't even be in this movie
if it wasn't for you.

35:36.783 --> 35:39.581
So thank you. That was really sweet.
- Mm.

35:39.719 --> 35:42.313
This guy right here,
we got a real civilian here.

35:42.455 --> 35:45.015
C'mon, William, tell us.
Wh-what do you do, uh...

35:45.158 --> 35:48.992
- I-I don't do anything important.
I take pictures. It's... very boring.

35:49.128 --> 35:51.653
- Oh, shit.
You're not paparazzi, are you?

35:51.798 --> 35:53.322
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>
- No.

35:53.466 --> 35:56.924
I actually, uh...
mostly stick to real people, so...

35:57.069 --> 35:59.833
- Billy is a private investigator.
He used to be a cop.

35:59.972 --> 36:02.213
- Get outta here. You serious?
- Is that how you two met?

36:02.308 --> 36:05.106
You promised not to write her a ticket
if she goes out with you.

36:05.244 --> 36:07.269
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>
- Yeah, something like that.

36:07.413 --> 36:09.847
- Well, details, details, tell us everything.
- Come on, Billy, details.

36:09.982 --> 36:12.507
How'd a guy like you end up
with a girl like Natalie?

36:12.652 --> 36:15.018
- A guy like me?
- Ah, I can't imagine

36:15.154 --> 36:17.645
you were too big on the theatre.
- This is you guys' party.

36:17.790 --> 36:19.991
Let's talk about your movie.
I'd rather hear about that.

36:20.092 --> 36:22.356
- No. No one leaves this table
without singing the blues, Billy.

36:22.495 --> 36:25.692
Natalie, you gotta pick up the slack here.
How did you meet this charming guy?

36:25.832 --> 36:29.734
- Billy was a friend of the family.
- Ah, so you guys lived

36:29.869 --> 36:32.497
in the same neighbourhood, or...?
- He worked by where I lived.

36:32.638 --> 36:34.868
- So you fell in love
with the neighbourhood policeman?

36:35.675 --> 36:36.972
C'mon.

36:37.109 --> 36:40.670
- We were just a bunch of broke Puerto Ricans
that nobody gave a damn about.

36:40.813 --> 36:42.542
And Billy was good to us.
- Barrow?

36:42.682 --> 36:44.343
Is that Puerto Rican?

36:44.483 --> 36:45.916
- It's actually Barea.

36:46.052 --> 36:47.644
- Nat... Natalie Barea.

36:47.787 --> 36:50.688
- Natalia.
- That actually has nice little ring to it.

36:50.823 --> 36:52.484
- Yeah.
- Okay, you changed it

36:52.625 --> 36:54.855
so you could play more Anglo?
- No.

36:55.862 --> 36:57.727
I changed it because...

36:57.864 --> 36:59.957
I was tired of going into auditions

37:00.099 --> 37:03.091
and the first question
out of the casting director's mouth

37:03.236 --> 37:05.704
was if I was related to Yesenia Barea.

37:06.873 --> 37:08.272
- Who's that?

37:08.407 --> 37:11.069
- My sister.
- Is she famous or somethin'?

37:11.210 --> 37:13.906
- Yeah. Her face was in all the papers
about seven years ago.

37:14.046 --> 37:16.606
- Nat. Please, don't...
- Beautiful 16-year-old girl

37:16.749 --> 37:20.014
found raped and beaten to death
in an abandoned apartment in Bolton Village.

37:26.525 --> 37:28.288
Billy was good to us.

37:28.427 --> 37:30.054
It was a really hard time and...

37:31.330 --> 37:33.093
...he made it better.

37:39.739 --> 37:41.331
<font color="#D900D9">(DISTANT SIRENS)</font>

37:41.741 --> 37:44.608
<i>- Well, sure, that's because you like
to accuse anyone who doesn't agree</i>

37:44.744 --> 37:47.440
with letting the rich off scot-free
of engaging in class warfare

37:47.580 --> 37:50.981
when in reality you know full well
what real class warfare is:

37:51.117 --> 37:53.278
stealing the homes of working people
in Bolton Village,

37:53.286 --> 37:56.119
and handing them over at a cut rate
to an investment bank.

37:56.255 --> 37:58.314
That, sir, is real class warfare.

37:58.457 --> 38:00.516
- Well, maybe where you grew up
in Connecticut,

38:00.660 --> 38:02.287
$3 billion is considered cut-rate,

38:02.428 --> 38:03.793
but here in New York City,

38:03.930 --> 38:07.297
$3 billion is considered a lot of money
that can solve a lot of problems.

38:07.433 --> 38:10.473
- All due respect, you don't solve problems
by bending over for billionaires.

38:10.603 --> 38:13.037
- Oh, I may bend over for billionaires,
but, you know what?

38:13.172 --> 38:14.969
You come from a long line of 'em.

38:15.107 --> 38:19.066
And, by the way, how are the renovations
coming on that $4 million townhouse of yours

38:19.211 --> 38:21.941
over in Brooklyn Heights?
- You want my house, too? Take it.

38:22.081 --> 38:25.050
I'm upside-down on my mortgage
like the rest of this city.

38:25.184 --> 38:27.812
Because the system has been rigged
by men like you.

38:31.390 --> 38:32.823
- Fuck, that's good.
- Yeah?

38:32.959 --> 38:35.826
- I like that. You make that stick,
you pull undecideds off the fence.

38:35.962 --> 38:38.157
- Okay.
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

38:38.297 --> 38:40.162
Alright. We need that moment. Paul.

38:40.299 --> 38:43.291
You know that, uh, "Senator,
you are no Jack Kennedy." That moment.

38:43.436 --> 38:45.336
And it's got to be Bolton Village-related.

38:45.471 --> 38:47.591
- I'm telling you, it's good.
You stick to the issues,

38:47.640 --> 38:49.835
people will see the difference
between the two of you.

38:49.976 --> 38:51.176
- It's not clean enough, Paul.

38:51.243 --> 38:54.770
It's gotta be clean-cut.
He's got this clear line of attack on me.

38:54.914 --> 38:57.508
I'm the rich Connecticut carpetbagger.
What the hell is he?

38:57.650 --> 39:00.619
- He's out of a job come Tuesday
if you stick to the fuckin' issues.

39:00.753 --> 39:02.380
- You're missing the point!
He's a crook!

39:02.521 --> 39:04.614
I need to be able to hammer that home

39:04.757 --> 39:07.624
when he taunts me and pokes at me
about my family money,

39:07.760 --> 39:11.389
Harvard and all the rest of it.
I need to be able to lay his fat ass flat!

39:11.530 --> 39:14.021
You, sir, are a crook and a liar!
And if he tries

39:14.166 --> 39:18.034
to challenge me to prove it,
I pull out that glorious piece of paper

39:18.170 --> 39:20.297
you said you'd provide
and I start reading out loud.

39:20.439 --> 39:22.964
- Let's take 10.
Can I talk to you for a minute?

39:23.442 --> 39:25.842
Alright, so what's your problem, Jack?

39:26.012 --> 39:28.310
- The Daily News is my problem, Paul.

39:28.447 --> 39:31.041
The <i>Post</i>, the <i>Times</i>, they're all the same.
Pick one.

39:31.183 --> 39:33.708
We got Hostetler backing up
a dump-truckload of shit on me

39:33.853 --> 39:36.879
and our campaign's coming up with piss-all
by the way of pushback.

39:37.023 --> 39:40.424
I thought that's what Montauk was all about.
What happened to that source of yours?

39:40.559 --> 39:42.459
- I'm working on it.
- So that's why you disappeared

39:42.595 --> 39:44.290
for nine hours yesterday?
- He kept us waiting.

39:44.430 --> 39:47.422
Kept us on the hook. I told you.
- You came back stinking of booze.

39:47.566 --> 39:50.262
- I had a fucking cocktail, sweetheart.
- So where is our pushback, then?

39:50.403 --> 39:54.100
- Our pushback are truth and facts, Jack.
That's how we play.

39:54.240 --> 39:56.401
- Where are our headlines?
That's all I wanna know.

39:56.542 --> 39:58.783
- I'll tell you something.
We don't need headlines, Jack.

39:58.911 --> 40:00.752
We don't need headlines,
because we're winning.

40:00.780 --> 40:03.010
Even their internal polling
has us up by three.

40:03.149 --> 40:05.014
You're winning on your own fucking terms.

40:05.151 --> 40:07.085
But let me tell you something,

40:07.219 --> 40:11.622
you go onto that debate stage
and you try to win that debate

40:11.757 --> 40:15.557
by going negative blow to negative blow,
he'll fuckin' destroy you.

40:15.694 --> 40:17.127
Understand that.

40:17.263 --> 40:19.595
- Glad you got so much faith in me, Paul.

40:19.732 --> 40:22.064
- I'm all faith, you smug sonofabitch.

40:22.902 --> 40:25.598
Why don't you try having some?
- Just do me a favour.

40:25.738 --> 40:27.205
Just do your job.

40:29.408 --> 40:31.376
Just get me that file.

40:32.912 --> 40:34.539
- Yes, sir.

40:35.514 --> 40:38.039
<font color="#D900D9">(SLOW JAZZY MUSIC)</font>

40:47.193 --> 40:50.629
- Hey, Murdock.
Save some for the rest of us, will you?

40:50.763 --> 40:52.958
- Mm, Billy, God, holy shit.

40:53.099 --> 40:55.727
What are you doing here?
- I was in the neighbourhood.

40:55.935 --> 40:57.402
- Yeah, me, too.

40:57.536 --> 41:00.562
- You club a herd of penguins for that getup?
- This number? What can I say?

41:00.706 --> 41:03.174
Private sector's been good to me.
- Oh, you a shamus?

41:03.309 --> 41:04.799
- Nah, security.

41:04.944 --> 41:06.605
See that kid over there?

41:06.745 --> 41:08.406
That's T odd Lancaster. That's my charge.

41:08.547 --> 41:10.811
Rich kid.
Pop tears down buildings for a living,

41:10.950 --> 41:13.248
wants him to run the business one day.

41:13.385 --> 41:15.910
I'm making sure he stays
on the straight and narrow till then.

41:16.055 --> 41:17.989
- How you doin', Mr. Mayor?
- Tony, how are you?

41:18.124 --> 41:20.115
Harris, come and say hello.

41:22.128 --> 41:24.596
This is Harris Sargent,
SVP at Solstein Donagan.

41:24.730 --> 41:27.198
Helped me push through
the Bolton Village deal.

41:27.333 --> 41:30.530
Four billion dollars
we beat out of this poor bastard.

41:30.669 --> 41:33.331
- Hi, Mr. Sargent. Good to see you.
You remember my son, Todd?

41:33.472 --> 41:35.235
- Todd.
- If you do, you get a prize.

41:35.374 --> 41:37.604
- Todd, when are you gonna
do the world a favour

41:37.743 --> 41:41.440
and take the business from your old man?
- When I die and he grows a pair.

41:41.580 --> 41:43.343
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>
- Oh, shit.

41:44.183 --> 41:45.707
- Some fuckin' party here, huh?

41:45.851 --> 41:48.684
- I'd rather be home watching the Knicks.
- Do what, lose?

41:48.821 --> 41:51.984
This is the best game in town, babe.
You got the commissioner over there.

41:52.791 --> 41:56.693
It's the worst-kept secret on earth,
him and the mayor can't stand each other.

41:56.829 --> 42:00.526
But the commish don't miss a party.
It's like watching Italian opera, them two.

42:00.666 --> 42:02.634
- What the hell do you know about opera?

42:02.768 --> 42:04.201
- Just 'cause I don't understand
the language,

42:04.336 --> 42:06.236
don't mean they ain't out
to fuck each other.

42:06.372 --> 42:08.636
Alright?
- Suite 5101, Mr. Taggart.

42:08.774 --> 42:10.674
I'm told it's urgent.

42:10.809 --> 42:12.174
- Excuse me.

42:13.179 --> 42:15.374
- In the neighbourhood, my ass.

42:35.401 --> 42:37.835
- May I offer you a drink, Mr. Taggart?

42:39.038 --> 42:40.505
- I don't drink.

42:40.639 --> 42:42.630
- But you used to. I can tell.

42:44.043 --> 42:45.067
- How?

42:45.211 --> 42:48.544
- By those three seconds you let pass
before turning down the drink.

42:49.048 --> 42:50.845
How long has it been?

42:51.650 --> 42:53.641
- Seven years.
- Good for you.

42:55.054 --> 42:57.352
Finally hit rock bottom, huh?

42:57.489 --> 42:59.457
- I did it to keep a woman.

42:59.592 --> 43:01.287
- Then you do believe in love.

43:01.427 --> 43:04.362
- I believe in lovin' the one you're with.
- Hmm. What are you,

43:04.496 --> 43:06.555
stupid or Catholic?

43:07.666 --> 43:08.928
- Both.

43:09.068 --> 43:11.059
- To your health, Mr. Taggart.

43:17.243 --> 43:20.440
- Well... perhaps you could explain
what I'm doin' up here?

43:22.248 --> 43:24.546
- Being tailed is exhausting.

43:25.684 --> 43:29.552
If I might pry for a moment, how much
are you being paid for your efforts?

43:29.688 --> 43:32.748
- Which efforts are those?
- The work you're doing for the mayor.

43:35.094 --> 43:36.959
I'll give you $50,000

43:37.096 --> 43:39.087
to give it up.
- Well, that's very generous,

43:39.231 --> 43:41.825
but I got a contract with the mayor.
- Break it.

43:41.967 --> 43:44.333
- You don't break contract with the mayor.

43:44.470 --> 43:47.337
- Don't I know it.
- Why don't you just leave him?

43:47.473 --> 43:49.964
- This is not what you think it is,
Mr. Taggart.

43:50.109 --> 43:52.839
- I take pictures, Mrs. Hostetler.
I don't get paid to think.

43:52.978 --> 43:56.175
- If the last seven years of your life
mean anything,

43:56.315 --> 44:00.251
if that woman you put down the bottle for
means anything... walk...

44:00.386 --> 44:01.785
away.

44:01.920 --> 44:03.979
Because if you think
you're investigating adultery,

44:04.123 --> 44:07.820
Mr. Taggart, you don't know
Nicholas Hostetler very well.

44:20.239 --> 44:21.831
- I see you've met Billy.

44:21.974 --> 44:23.498
- Yes, we met.

44:24.310 --> 44:26.608
- Did he tell you
he's doing some work for me?

44:26.745 --> 44:30.010
- He mentioned it.
- Did he mention it was exclusive?

44:30.149 --> 44:31.673
- Yes, he did.

44:31.817 --> 44:34.149
- You used to know what exclusive meant,
dear.

44:34.520 --> 44:37.284
In this case, it means I worked for it...

44:38.157 --> 44:40.455
...keep your grubby little paws off it.

44:41.960 --> 44:43.393
- Poor Nicky.

44:43.529 --> 44:46.327
You never did learn how to share, did you?

44:46.965 --> 44:50.765
Well, don't worry...
I'll teach you before it's too late.

44:52.104 --> 44:53.537
- Careful, dear.

44:53.972 --> 44:55.337
- You, too, darling.

44:57.176 --> 44:59.167
Mr. Taggart, please take care.

45:04.183 --> 45:05.480
- I need a drink.

45:11.557 --> 45:13.354
What have you got for me?

45:14.193 --> 45:16.388
- Actually, Mayor,
I think I need a few more days.

45:16.528 --> 45:18.291
I'm pretty sure I got things nailed down,

45:18.430 --> 45:20.489
I just wanna take another 48 hours
to confirm.

45:23.369 --> 45:27.931
- You have an envelope... of photographs
in your pocket.

45:28.073 --> 45:31.065
That I paid for. Right?

45:31.210 --> 45:32.199
Right?

45:32.811 --> 45:34.676
Burning a hole in your bleeding heart?

45:53.599 --> 45:54.759
Good work.

46:02.841 --> 46:04.536
Alright, Billy, we're done.

46:12.351 --> 46:14.251
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING AND CHEERING)</font>

46:18.857 --> 46:21.485
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Hey, Ryan, you excited tonight?<font color="#808080">
WOMAN:</font> Ryan!

46:21.627 --> 46:23.618
<font color="#D900D9">(REPORTERS CLAMOURING)</font>

46:23.762 --> 46:25.923
- Whoa!
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

46:26.064 --> 46:28.294
Whoo!

46:33.939 --> 46:35.873
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)</font>

46:41.280 --> 46:43.805
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)</font>

46:47.286 --> 46:49.083
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)</font>

46:49.455 --> 46:51.286
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> You go, Natalie!

46:52.958 --> 46:56.257
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Yeah, Natalie! Whoo-hoo!
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)</font>

46:58.897 --> 47:02.094
<i>- I love the line
between the sky and the water.</i>

47:02.668 --> 47:05.159
<i>You see how it gets darker
the farther it is away,</i>

47:05.304 --> 47:06.771
<i>and it's just a line</i>

47:06.905 --> 47:08.964
<i>separating sky from water.</i>

47:09.107 --> 47:11.041
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

47:11.176 --> 47:14.043
<i>He's religious.
I get it, he's gotta have hope.</i>

47:14.179 --> 47:16.010
<i>He's gotta have something to believe in.</i>

47:16.148 --> 47:19.276
<i>- Why do you have to bring him up?
What does it matter?</i>

47:19.418 --> 47:21.886
<i>Not everything in this life
is black and white.</i>

47:22.020 --> 47:24.955
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>
<i>Let's not talk about him anymore.</i>

47:25.924 --> 47:27.118
<i>- Let's go.</i>

47:32.331 --> 47:34.322
<font color="#D900D9">(HEAVY BREATHING AND MOANING)</font>

47:41.340 --> 47:42.307
<i>- Ah!</i>

47:47.946 --> 47:49.345
<font color="#D900D9">(MOANING)</font>

47:51.783 --> 47:54.479
<font color="#D900D9">(HIP HOP PLAYING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

47:55.954 --> 47:58.013
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Kiss of Life!<font color="#808080">
ALL:</font> Kiss of Life!

47:58.156 --> 48:00.522
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING)</font><font color="#808080">
MAN:</font> Sundance, here we come!

48:02.694 --> 48:05.720
- Alright.
- Pretty trippy. Like it?

48:06.532 --> 48:09.092
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> It's beautiful.<font color="#808080">
NATALIE:</font> Really?

48:09.234 --> 48:10.531
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

48:12.738 --> 48:14.831
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

48:14.973 --> 48:17.965
- Can I get a double Jameson, please?
- Yeah, you got it.

48:40.332 --> 48:42.357
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

48:44.069 --> 48:46.629
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING)</font><font color="#808080">
TAGGART:</font> Again.

48:46.772 --> 48:49.935
- You want a water back for that?
- Just pour the fucking drink, please.

48:50.075 --> 48:52.202
Thank you.
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHING)</font>

48:52.344 --> 48:53.868
- Billy, what are you doing?

48:54.012 --> 48:55.445
- Hey, Nat, I just...

48:55.581 --> 48:58.448
I just didn't wanna be the only one
not celebrating.

48:58.584 --> 49:00.643
- Billy, don't do this.
- It's a party, right?

49:00.786 --> 49:05.780
And what a fucking movie that was, Nat.
I mean, my God, I never seen you that good.

49:06.224 --> 49:08.454
I mean, that was incredible.
You were so convincing.

49:08.594 --> 49:11.791
- Excuse me.
Can you take this drink back, please?

49:11.930 --> 49:14.091
- Please, okay? I'm fine.
- Billy, don't!

49:14.232 --> 49:15.790
That's enough.
- What?

49:16.535 --> 49:19.299
What?
- You promised me, Billy.

49:19.438 --> 49:21.998
How can you hurt me like this?
- How can I hurt you?

49:22.140 --> 49:25.180
You haven't once asked me how I'm feeling...
- This is not your night, Billy.

49:25.310 --> 49:28.905
I've worked so hard for this.
It doesn't mean anything to you, does it?

49:29.047 --> 49:32.574
You know, why don't you go do a line, too?
Go back to being the old Billy,

49:32.718 --> 49:34.652
'cause everybody knows
what a great guy he was.

49:34.786 --> 49:37.687
I'm gonna go hang out with my friends.
- You mean Ryan?

49:37.823 --> 49:40.348
What, d'you fuck him?
- Don't do this.

49:40.492 --> 49:42.153
- Fine. I'll go ask him myself.
- Billy.

49:42.294 --> 49:43.921
Just go home. Please?

