01:22:01.031 --> 01:22:04.797
<i>or are we being treated
to a Nick Hostetler soliloquy?</i>

01:22:04.935 --> 01:22:06.596
The issue is dire.

01:22:06.736 --> 01:22:09.432
Because you and your cronies
have rigged the game.

01:22:09.573 --> 01:22:13.907
And honest, hardworking New Yorkers
recognize that nothing will change.

01:22:14.044 --> 01:22:17.741
Nothing will ever change
if we continue to elect men like this.

01:22:17.881 --> 01:22:20.008
- Tell me things have not changed!

01:22:20.584 --> 01:22:22.711
When I was elected mayor,

01:22:22.852 --> 01:22:25.446
this was a broken city.
Broken.

01:22:25.589 --> 01:22:28.456
Step by step, I've been getting it fixed.

01:22:28.592 --> 01:22:32.084
Bolton Village
is just another one of those steps.

01:22:32.228 --> 01:22:33.525
Tell me things haven't changed.

01:22:33.663 --> 01:22:37.656
I just stood before you all
and told you we have a $3 billion surplus...

01:22:37.801 --> 01:22:40.326
- Mayor...
- Tell me things haven't changed.

01:22:40.470 --> 01:22:42.438
No other mayor
in the history of this great city

01:22:42.572 --> 01:22:45.336
has been able to stand in front of the people
and tell them that!

01:22:45.475 --> 01:22:48.156
When you step out of your house,
in the morning, with your children,

01:22:48.178 --> 01:22:50.908
you take 'em to the parks
of the five boroughs, d'you feel safe?

01:22:51.047 --> 01:22:52.446
Yes, you do,

01:22:52.582 --> 01:22:55.142
'cause I get your letters and I know you do.

01:22:55.285 --> 01:22:57.810
That's us, working together,
getting it fixed.

01:22:57.954 --> 01:22:59.751
Tell me things haven't changed.

