01:38:01.323 --> 01:38:04.759
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> He was very charming, indeed, yes.

01:38:04.894 --> 01:38:06.885
- Ahem. Ladies and gentlemen,

01:38:07.029 --> 01:38:10.590
unaccustomed as I am to public speaking,
I know you, Sam, you like a debate.

01:38:10.733 --> 01:38:13.031
How did you enjoy that one?
- Masterful.

01:38:13.168 --> 01:38:14.969
<font color="#D900D9">(MAYOR CHUCKLING)</font>
- Thank you very, very much.

01:38:14.970 --> 01:38:17.803
Uh, firstly,
I'd like to thank you all for coming.

01:38:17.940 --> 01:38:22.843
This is a room full of my wife and I's
very, very good friends, so thank you.

01:38:22.978 --> 01:38:26.414
A man much smarter than me once said
that politics...

01:38:26.549 --> 01:38:28.847
is the art of the possible.

01:38:28.984 --> 01:38:32.977
Now, this afternoon,
Jack Valliant was ordering stationery.

01:38:33.756 --> 01:38:36.850
Tonight, he's looking for the number
of the bus that hit him.

01:38:36.992 --> 01:38:39.222
He fought a good fight,
but he was boxing shadows.

01:38:39.361 --> 01:38:42.057
He was like Roberto Duran out there.
<i>"No mas, Nicky, no mas.</i>

01:38:42.197 --> 01:38:44.893
Don't hit me no more."
- Mr. Mayor. He says it's urgent.

01:38:45.034 --> 01:38:47.628
- Thank... I'll deal with this.
I... I apol... Don't go anywhere.

01:38:47.770 --> 01:38:49.635
I have a lot of people to thank.

01:38:49.772 --> 01:38:51.262
Yes.
<i>- It's me.</i>

01:38:51.407 --> 01:38:54.137
- Billy.
I didn't think you'd call me so soon.

01:38:54.276 --> 01:38:57.074
<i>- Look out your window now, Mayor.
It's your future.</i>

01:38:57.212 --> 01:38:59.009
- I think your ride's here, Nick.

01:39:05.588 --> 01:39:09.422
- Nicholas Hostetler, you're under arrest
for the murder of Paul Andrews.

01:39:09.558 --> 01:39:11.082
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> What?
<font color="#D900D9">(MURMURINGS)</font>

01:39:11.226 --> 01:39:14.662
- You have the right to remain silent.
Anything you say can and will be used

01:39:14.797 --> 01:39:17.595
against you in a court of law.
- Will be used against you, Carl.

01:39:17.733 --> 01:39:19.257
- You have the right to an attorney.

01:39:19.401 --> 01:39:21.892
If you cannot afford one,
one will be provided to you.

01:39:22.037 --> 01:39:25.097
- Attorneys? They'll be pulling
your dental records once I'm done with you.

01:39:25.240 --> 01:39:26.639
- Do you understand these rights

01:39:26.775 --> 01:39:29.107
as I have described them to you?
- I understand you're suicidal.

01:39:29.244 --> 01:39:31.872
You may have forgotten
how you got your job; I have not.

01:39:32.448 --> 01:39:36.714
Do you really think a jury of my peers
in New York City will convict me?

01:39:37.052 --> 01:39:39.247
- I'm just the handcuffs guy.

01:39:40.155 --> 01:39:41.918
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD MURMURING)</font>

01:39:42.057 --> 01:39:45.049
- Don't wait up, dear.
- Have I ever?

01:39:50.265 --> 01:39:52.233
- I guess we both misjudged Billy, Mayor.

01:39:52.368 --> 01:39:54.700
Then again, you misjudged the lot of us.

01:39:54.837 --> 01:39:56.737
You thought Billy would roll over,

01:39:56.872 --> 01:39:59.500
you thought Andrews
was sleeping with your wife.

01:39:59.642 --> 01:40:01.269
You thought I wasn't.

01:40:02.645 --> 01:40:04.909
- Mr. Mayor!
<font color="#D900D9">(REPORTERS CLAMOURING)</font>

01:40:06.081 --> 01:40:08.641
Why did you do it?
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMOURING)</font>

01:40:17.660 --> 01:40:19.855
What does this mean for the election?!

01:40:29.672 --> 01:40:31.299
<font color="#D900D9">(DISTANT SIRENS)</font>

01:40:33.509 --> 01:40:37.206
<i>- Councilman, New Yorkers have been put
through quite an ordeal these last few days,</i>

01:40:37.346 --> 01:40:39.974
<i>beginning with the murder of Paul Andrews,
your campaign manager,</i>

01:40:40.115 --> 01:40:42.015
<i>and culminating last night with the arrest</i>

01:40:42.151 --> 01:40:43.778
<i>of Mayor Hostetler
in connection with that crime.</i>

01:40:43.919 --> 01:40:45.853
<i>What do you have to say to New Yorkers</i>

01:40:45.988 --> 01:40:49.515
<i>who quite frankly have lost faith
in their government?</i>

01:40:49.692 --> 01:40:52.991
<i>- Well, days like these
can definitely shake your faith...</i>

01:40:53.128 --> 01:40:56.188
- Rachel, you stayin' out of trouble?
- Hey... Trying.

01:40:56.331 --> 01:40:57.696
- Yeah, I know it.

01:41:00.536 --> 01:41:02.128
Whatever he's drinking.

01:41:09.545 --> 01:41:11.536
Tomorrow's the big day, huh, Billy?

01:41:11.680 --> 01:41:14.945
<font color="#808080">VALLIANT:</font> <i>... believed that whenever
there's a sliver of a choice...</i>

01:41:15.084 --> 01:41:17.348
- Looks like our guy's a lock.

01:41:22.925 --> 01:41:24.654
To Jack Valliant.

01:41:27.730 --> 01:41:29.459
A good man.
- <i>... We need every ounce</i>

01:41:29.598 --> 01:41:32.726
<i>that we can muster
to repair the damage that's been done.</i>

01:41:43.746 --> 01:41:46.943
- I, uh... I got you... this.

01:41:47.716 --> 01:41:51.516
- What is it?
- What does it look like? It's a phone card.

01:41:55.958 --> 01:41:57.391
- Thank you.

01:41:58.393 --> 01:41:59.951
- Every time, Billy.

01:42:08.237 --> 01:42:10.967
- It's okay, Katy. I'll be home real soon.

01:42:11.774 --> 01:42:13.435
- I'll be here.

01:42:13.575 --> 01:42:14.974
- C'mon, Billy.

01:42:15.778 --> 01:42:17.769
We'll take the long way.

